I believe that a parents ultimate goal for their children is simultaneously the hardest for us. 

To make ourselves obsolete. 

We need future leads, kids are feel safe and empowered as adults to make their own decisions,  how to have health relationships.

For a child, everything is an experiment, from which they learn. 

Let your child explore his world,  make his own mistakes without judgements, allow them an appropriate level of autonomy. 

When we are gone, we can be at peace knowing our kids will make the right decision for them, with confidence  and love.

It's so important as parents that we constantly monitor our actions,  thoughts and words around our children.

You may have a fleeting moment that affect your kids forever.

Teach em good habit.

This past 6 months have definitely been the most difficult period I have ever gone through on a multitude  of levels.

Went through some crippling anxiety attack and severe depression from it.

Also went from 202 to 158 in 4 weeks. (173 now).

But it has also been a great time for me to be "awake" and see things and people for what and who they are.

This time has been transformation in nature.  The Ultimate "lemons into lemonade " scenario. 

I've learned a lot about myself, who I am as a father and what Jason's values,  beliefs and boundaries all look like.

That's the amazing thing about kids, your whole day/mood can change when they smile, laughter or want you to hold them.

We must always put our kids first, no matter the cost.  If it wasn't for my amazing friends that have reached out and for my kids,  I don't know that I would be getting through  this.

Thank you all for the love and support. 

I hope you smile today as big as this little guys.

So heartbroken to hear about my buddy Stephen Bonnar's passing. 

If you live in the Chicago area , he was a household name at local MMA event. 

I was lucky enough to be on several cards with him and Miguel Torres way back in the late 90'.

I met Stephen through Carlson Gracie Sr at his school downtown.  Stephen was always a solid boxer and was just adding to his ground game.

It's especially hard to see guys that watched the sport , truly evolve from the days of events begin "NHB" or "Vale Tudo"
To where it is now. 

You had to love prove yourself back in those days.  Simply put, there was no money in the sport. 

It WAS fight club.  A (slightly) better and more efficient version of, where we had guy lying about records,  Weigh ins  that never actually happened. To rule changes the day is the fight. 

Stephen and I have stayed in contact over the years and at one point per ufc,  even worked with my Dad at roadway.

There is no debate, his fight w @forrestgriffin was the single most important bout in UFC Histroy.

RIP Legend. Sleep well my brother

I never ask this, but if you feel the same way, please tag someone to spread the word.  Feel free to DM me privately. 

A fighters' career is short, and their lives afterward should  not be due to addiction . They developed as part of their love for fighting

I made a similar offer to Logan in 2020.

I will give Jake Paul props. He is a great promoter, and hand picks fights well.  He is also a much better boxer than most give him credit God's.

 That said,  the Diaz fight is never going to happen, and before you start calling out legends who have nothing to gain by fighting you, coupled with the fact that you have to earn those big fights. 

Why don't you show the world you can beat up a 42yo retired MMA fighter first.

Because you would look silly when I choke you unconscious.

You're ready for Nate? Prove it.  I'm your huckleberry
Bathtime w little man!

Dear @JakePaul, don't be scared.

How are you gonna try to call out legends of the sport when you can't even beat a 42 yo retired fighter.

I'll choke that silly beard off your face in rd1 in the name of all of the athletes that truly sacrificed and earned the opportunity to fight in a big show.

You have done a great job marketing yourself and hand picking opponents,  but it's insulting to every MMA fighter to think you can walk in off some Influencer status and call out guys that have put blood, sweat and tears into this sport for years.

How about you prove you can beat me before you run that mouth.

If you do, you can say you beat "the human weapon " and make yourself another belt

Don't be scared.

I've never given much weight to what someone says they are going to do. 

Because it can fail for a multitude of reasons, the main being that they just don't truly care enough to follow through. 

Always watch action.  Do not be fooled by a silver tongue.

Watch what someone does. Not says.

What they say is who they want to World to believe they are.

What they DO, is who they truly are.

Be AWAKE

Pressure, pressure, pressure. 

When we pressure our opponent from crosside, we make them exert more force to escape. 

This typically leads to them exposing the back of the triceps and allows us easy access to a head and arm choke. 

Simple, yet VERY effective.

Understanding the difference between dealing with a standing opponent and one who chooses to pass on the knees is paramount.

There are distinct advantages and disadvantages of being in each position.

Having a game plan and the ability to lead your opponent down the road to your submission is only obtained once you have the ability to 

1. identify what your goals are, 

2. what your opponents' goals from a position are and 

3. fluidity linking moves together to keep pushing them down our path.

#BJJ #bjjchokes #butterflysweep

Toss back Tues to when @dominickcruz and I were calling #ShootoBrazil for @UFCFightPass. 

It was my 1st time in the play by play role (both Bellator and One Champion, I was color), and man, is it much harder. 

Making it even more challenging was Dom and I as well as UFC production, were at the mercy of the highly disorganized Shoot broadcast. 

I would get a countdown in my ear that "A fighter was walking in 5, 4, 3,2, ...wait....now we are on a wide shot of the city....ok now we are showing a tale of the tape from the previous match. Then , we would return to the venue, and both fighters were already in the ring. Lol

Twas a fun time. Thanks to @UFC for the opportunity!

#mma #shootobrazil #ufcfightpass #broadcasting #commentator
